00:06:11,429 --> 00:06:14,165
♪ Who, who, who, who? ♪

00:06:14,165 --> 00:06:17,268
♪ Who... are you? ♪

00:06:17,268 --> 00:06:19,170
♪ Who, who, who, who? ♪

00:06:19,170 --> 00:06:20,838
♪ I really wanna know ♪

00:06:20,838 --> 00:06:23,541
♪ Who... are you? ♪

00:06:23,541 --> 00:06:25,476
♪ Oh-oh-oh ♪
♪ <i>Who... ♪</i>

00:06:25,476 --> 00:06:29,080
♪ Come on, tell me who are you,
you, you ♪

00:06:29,080 --> 00:06:31,449
♪ Are you! ♪

00:06:36,487 --> 00:06:38,589
COMPUTER VOICE:
<i>You are going the wrong way.</i>

00:06:38,589 --> 00:06:40,391
Make a U-turn at the next
intersection.

00:06:40,391 --> 00:06:43,361
Intersection?
You are going the wrong way.

00:06:43,361 --> 00:06:45,262
There's no road!

00:06:45,262 --> 00:06:46,897
You are going the wrong way.

00:06:46,897 --> 00:06:48,499
Recalculating.

00:06:59,176 --> 00:07:00,845
(tires screech)

00:07:00,845 --> 00:07:02,179
You have arrived
at your destination.

00:07:07,318 --> 00:07:09,120
Your dad teach you how to drive?

00:07:09,120 --> 00:07:12,223
Funny. You guys could use
a few more freeways around here.

00:07:12,223 --> 00:07:14,325
Who's inside?

00:07:14,325 --> 00:07:16,427
Me and Greg. You want
to take the perimeter?

00:07:16,427 --> 00:07:18,195
I got my sunscreen.

00:07:18,195 --> 00:07:20,064
Ah, there you go.

00:07:20,064 --> 00:07:21,365
Oh, speak of the devil,
there's the old man there.

00:07:22,500 --> 00:07:25,536
Enjoy yourself. (chuckles)

00:07:25,536 --> 00:07:27,571
Hey, Conrad,
how you doing?
Nick.

00:07:27,571 --> 00:07:30,007
Good to see ya.

00:07:30,007 --> 00:07:32,543
(siren wailing)

00:07:32,543 --> 00:07:34,011
Cigars?

00:07:34,011 --> 00:07:35,079
Kills the decomp.

00:07:35,079 --> 00:07:37,381
I always had
a few on hand.

00:07:37,381 --> 00:07:39,283
So, uh, you settling in?

00:07:39,283 --> 00:07:40,551
Yeah.

00:07:42,620 --> 00:07:44,889
You make an appearance
at every crime scene?

00:07:44,889 --> 00:07:46,891
I usually roll on
anything over a double.

00:07:46,891 --> 00:07:49,427
And this one, press is
gonna be all over it.

00:07:49,427 --> 00:07:50,828
I got stuff to do.

00:07:50,828 --> 00:07:52,830
REPORTER:
Undersheriff Ecklie!

00:07:52,830 --> 00:07:55,266
Is it true
you have a suspect in custody?

00:07:55,266 --> 00:07:57,401
Can you tell us if you
have any leads?
Can you tell
us if you have a suspect?

00:07:57,401 --> 00:08:00,538
Look, look, all I can say is we
have a person of interest

00:08:00,538 --> 00:08:02,440
<i>in custody and that we intend</i>
<i>to question him.</i>

00:08:02,440 --> 00:08:04,975
REPORTER: <i>Is there any</i>
<i>additional information</i>

00:08:04,975 --> 00:08:07,144
<i>you can share with the press?</i>
ECKLIE:
<i>As a matter of due diligence,</i>

00:08:07,144 --> 00:08:09,380
<i>we're performing a thorough</i>
<i>search of the neighborhood,</i>

00:08:09,380 --> 00:08:11,315
<i>including one of the</i>
<i>neighboring homes.</i>

00:08:23,093 --> 00:08:26,230
Uh, don't mean to interrupt
your search, but, uh,

00:08:26,230 --> 00:08:28,833
I've torn this place
apart-- there's no gun,

00:08:28,833 --> 00:08:30,868
no knife...
Did you notice the decor?

00:08:30,868 --> 00:08:32,403
You in the market
for a decorator?

00:08:32,403 --> 00:08:35,306
The kid's 27 years old.

00:08:35,306 --> 00:08:37,875
He answers phones
at a body shop.

00:08:37,875 --> 00:08:40,277
Yet all the furniture
in this place looks like

00:08:40,277 --> 00:08:41,612
it belongs to his parents.

00:08:41,612 --> 00:08:43,047
Like hand-me-downs.

00:08:43,047 --> 00:08:45,316
The only room that
reflects his taste

00:08:45,316 --> 00:08:47,117
is this one,

00:08:47,117 --> 00:08:49,453
and it's laid out
exactly like...

00:08:49,453 --> 00:08:51,455
like the dead
little girl's room.

00:08:51,455 --> 00:08:53,390
Even has the same dollhouse.

00:09:00,931 --> 00:09:02,833
WILLOWS:
Not <i>exactly</i> the same.

00:09:10,474 --> 00:09:12,610
Ahh...

00:09:15,479 --> 00:09:17,381
(scoffs)

00:09:19,350 --> 00:09:22,152
Guy lived just across the way.

00:09:22,152 --> 00:09:24,421
He's been watching
her for years.

00:09:24,421 --> 00:09:27,324
(camera shutter clicking)

00:09:45,409 --> 00:09:47,211
(shutter clicks)

00:10:00,624 --> 00:10:02,826
Sanders?

00:10:02,826 --> 00:10:04,194
I got boot prints.

00:10:04,194 --> 00:10:05,829
Me, too.

00:10:05,829 --> 00:10:07,331
(phone rings)
Mine have been
here a while.

00:10:07,331 --> 00:10:10,434
I think somebody made a habit
out of hiding back here.

00:10:10,434 --> 00:10:12,503
Yeah. Looking in.

00:10:12,503 --> 00:10:15,306
Just got a text
from Catherine.

00:10:15,306 --> 00:10:17,541
Our perp is a peeper.

00:10:17,541 --> 00:10:20,110
BRASS: Can I get you
anything?

00:10:20,110 --> 00:10:21,579
Want a soda, something?

00:10:21,579 --> 00:10:24,315
Cherry cola would be nice.

00:10:24,315 --> 00:10:25,349
I'm sure it would.

00:10:25,349 --> 00:10:27,918
I know what you think.

00:10:27,918 --> 00:10:30,921
(quietly): You're
just lucky I'm a cop.

00:10:33,557 --> 00:10:35,259
I'm CSI Willows

00:10:35,259 --> 00:10:36,493
here to process you.

00:10:36,493 --> 00:10:38,295
Get up.

00:10:43,434 --> 00:10:45,269
Step on the paper.

00:10:45,269 --> 00:10:47,237
Strip.

00:10:47,237 --> 00:10:49,273
Just pretend she's an
eight-year-old girl.

00:11:01,585 --> 00:11:03,454
Pants next.

00:11:03,454 --> 00:11:05,422
Could you close the blinds?

00:11:11,195 --> 00:11:12,429
BRASS:
Better?

00:11:25,442 --> 00:11:27,311
Keep going.

00:11:33,384 --> 00:11:35,119
PHILLIPS:
<i>Three in the van.</i>

00:11:35,119 --> 00:11:36,387
Still waiting on the mom.

00:11:36,387 --> 00:11:37,488
Thanks, David.

00:11:37,488 --> 00:11:39,423
(camera shutter clicking)

00:11:39,423 --> 00:11:42,960
ROBBINS:
Any reason you're holding her?

00:11:42,960 --> 00:11:44,962
I need her in context.

00:11:44,962 --> 00:11:47,197
There's a lot of
blood spatter here.

00:11:47,197 --> 00:11:50,834
There's a lot of blood
in this house, period.

00:11:50,834 --> 00:11:53,470
All this had to have taken
a lot of time.
Grandmother was

00:11:53,470 --> 00:11:56,073
stabbed a dozen times;
the father was shot

00:11:56,073 --> 00:11:57,241
three times.

00:12:04,548 --> 00:12:06,583
Guy has a knife and a gun.

00:12:06,583 --> 00:12:09,253
So why does he need
the towel bar?

00:12:11,155 --> 00:12:13,490
You really think one person
could've done all this?

00:12:19,997 --> 00:12:21,598
Cadets are outside
beating the bushes

00:12:21,598 --> 00:12:23,233
looking for the
knife and the gun.

00:12:23,233 --> 00:12:25,102
They're having
the same luck that we did.

00:12:25,102 --> 00:12:28,005
I've seen this freezer before.

00:12:28,005 --> 00:12:31,041
My wife and I once
went away for a weekend,

00:12:31,041 --> 00:12:33,277
and we left
our eldest in charge,

00:12:33,277 --> 00:12:34,578
God help us,
so the kids

00:12:34,578 --> 00:12:36,113
did all the shopping.

00:12:36,113 --> 00:12:38,115
When we came back,

00:12:38,115 --> 00:12:39,883
the freezer
looked just like this.

00:12:39,883 --> 00:12:41,852
SIDLE:
Popsicles, ice cream.

00:12:41,852 --> 00:12:43,487
It's a great way to lure a kid.

00:12:43,487 --> 00:12:46,523
Yeah. You know, not a lure,
more like a...

00:12:46,523 --> 00:12:49,293
a lifestyle.

00:12:49,293 --> 00:12:51,428
Arrested development.
You think

00:12:51,428 --> 00:12:54,431
John Lee likes little girls
because he's a little boy?

00:12:54,431 --> 00:12:56,100
Immature, isolated.

00:12:56,100 --> 00:12:59,069
You know, he hides,
takes pictures through windows.

00:12:59,069 --> 00:13:00,871
I'm passive;
I'm not aggressive.

00:13:00,871 --> 00:13:02,372
I thought you
liked to play dead,

00:13:02,372 --> 00:13:04,108
get into the head of the <i>victim.</i>

00:13:04,108 --> 00:13:05,909
You know, it depends--
you know, you walk

00:13:05,909 --> 00:13:07,377
into a room,
the victim, suspect.

00:13:07,377 --> 00:13:09,613
I go with whoever has
the best story to tell.

00:13:09,613 --> 00:13:11,381
What story is
this guy telling you?

00:13:11,381 --> 00:13:13,484
I don't know yet.

00:13:13,484 --> 00:13:17,921
But I'm not so sure that it ends
in a quadruple homicide.
Oh, whoa,

00:13:17,921 --> 00:13:19,857
you don't think
the man-boy did it?

00:13:19,857 --> 00:13:21,325
He was in their house,

00:13:21,325 --> 00:13:23,127
he... was holding

00:13:23,127 --> 00:13:25,028
the little girl's nightgown,
he watched her

00:13:25,028 --> 00:13:27,064
for years.
Yeah, exactly.

00:13:27,064 --> 00:13:28,565
For years. Thank you, yeah.

00:13:28,565 --> 00:13:31,068
And all of a sudden one night
he stops watching

00:13:31,068 --> 00:13:32,503
and he starts killing?

00:13:32,503 --> 00:13:35,105
Why?

00:13:35,105 --> 00:13:36,540
(gulps, shivers)

00:13:36,540 --> 00:13:38,175
WILLOWS:
Right hand.

00:13:39,276 --> 00:13:41,145
Is it gonna hurt?

00:13:41,145 --> 00:13:43,180
A lot less than
jabbing a towel bar

00:13:43,180 --> 00:13:44,848
into a woman 20 times.

00:13:44,848 --> 00:13:46,416
I didn't do it.

00:13:46,416 --> 00:13:48,318
Any of it.

00:13:48,318 --> 00:13:50,287
I went by the house.

00:13:50,287 --> 00:13:52,289
I looked in
and I saw her.

00:13:52,289 --> 00:13:53,924
She was already dead.

00:13:53,924 --> 00:13:56,560
The blood.

00:13:56,560 --> 00:13:57,928
(cap snaps on)

00:13:57,928 --> 00:13:59,363
I loved her.

00:13:59,363 --> 00:14:01,999
I couldn't leave her
there like that.

00:14:01,999 --> 00:14:03,500
Other hand.
BRASS:
You know,

00:14:03,500 --> 00:14:05,836
I ran you-- you had no
record, no complaints.

00:14:05,836 --> 00:14:07,604
But here's what
I think happened.

00:14:07,604 --> 00:14:09,306
I think you were hanging out

00:14:09,306 --> 00:14:11,875
by that window peeping,
and someone saw you,

00:14:11,875 --> 00:14:14,511
told the Chamblisses--
Dad didn't like that.

00:14:14,511 --> 00:14:17,915
So he walked across the
street to your house,

00:14:17,915 --> 00:14:20,851
knocked on your door,
then knocked on your head.

00:14:20,851 --> 00:14:23,554
And you didn't
like that.
I tested your hands

00:14:23,554 --> 00:14:25,989
for lead to determine
if you fired a gun.

00:14:25,989 --> 00:14:28,926
And guess what
color positive is?

00:14:30,961 --> 00:14:33,397
WILLOWS:
You shot that
little girl.

00:14:33,397 --> 00:14:37,034
You shot her father,
sliced and diced
her grandmother,

00:14:37,034 --> 00:14:39,369
and stabbed and beat her
mother with a towel bar.

00:14:39,369 --> 00:14:41,271
BRASS:
And we're gonna
prove it, too.

00:14:41,271 --> 00:14:44,374
So you got a choice-- you can
spend the rest of your life

00:14:44,374 --> 00:14:47,044
in general pop with a bunch
of gangsters and killers

00:14:47,044 --> 00:14:48,846
who never get to
see their kids,

00:14:48,846 --> 00:14:51,114
they're gonna take it out
on you in a heavy way,

00:14:51,114 --> 00:14:52,583
<i>or</i> you can tell us

00:14:52,583 --> 00:14:54,618
what you did...

00:14:54,618 --> 00:14:57,955
and maybe buy yourself a private
cell-- what's it gonna be?

00:14:57,955 --> 00:14:59,122
I did it.

00:15:02,326 --> 00:15:05,329
I'm the one who killed
the Chambliss family.

00:15:06,430 --> 00:15:07,965
(reporters clamoring)

00:15:07,965 --> 00:15:09,533
Good afternoon.

00:15:09,533 --> 00:15:11,001
I'm Undersheriff Ecklie

00:15:11,001 --> 00:15:13,303
of the Los Vegas
Police Department.

00:15:13,303 --> 00:15:15,205
I'm here to announce that,

00:15:15,205 --> 00:15:18,275
thanks to the fine efforts
of our detectives and CSI's,

00:15:18,275 --> 00:15:19,943
we have a suspect in custody

00:15:19,943 --> 00:15:22,913
who has confessed to the murders
of the Chambliss family.

00:15:22,913 --> 00:15:25,849
Can you tell us his name?
Why did he do it?
How did he it?

00:15:25,849 --> 00:15:27,551
I have no further comment
at this time.

00:15:27,551 --> 00:15:29,486
Why can't you tell us?
One last question.

00:15:29,486 --> 00:15:31,622
Hey, thanks.
Nice job.

00:15:31,622 --> 00:15:33,123
Good work, sir.
(chuckles):
Yeah.

00:15:35,158 --> 00:15:37,427
WOMAN:
I am saying there
has been a mistake.

00:15:37,427 --> 00:15:39,229
I saw the news--
that sheriff...

00:15:39,229 --> 00:15:41,164
OFFICER: Ma'am,
slow... down.

00:15:41,164 --> 00:15:43,100
WOMAN: Don't
patronize me.

00:15:43,100 --> 00:15:44,268
I have
information about

00:15:44,268 --> 00:15:45,535
the Chambliss murders.

00:15:45,535 --> 00:15:47,170
I need to talk
to somebody in charge.

00:15:47,170 --> 00:15:49,139
OFFICER: That would
be Captain Brass.
You arrested

00:15:49,139 --> 00:15:51,608
the wrong man!
WILLOWS:
Really?

00:15:51,608 --> 00:15:52,943
And you would
know that how?

00:15:54,378 --> 00:15:56,179
I know because I did it.

00:15:58,181 --> 00:16:01,151
I'm the one who killed
the Chambliss family.

00:16:15,966 --> 00:16:17,134
BRASS:
So...

00:16:17,134 --> 00:16:18,268
Leslie, uh...

00:16:18,268 --> 00:16:19,569
Gitig.

00:16:19,569 --> 00:16:21,338
Leslie Gitig.

00:16:21,338 --> 00:16:22,906
G-I-T-I-G.

00:16:22,906 --> 00:16:25,108
People always
get it wrong.
Well,

00:16:25,108 --> 00:16:27,911
we're gonna get
everything right today, Leslie.

00:16:27,911 --> 00:16:29,279
How do you know

00:16:29,279 --> 00:16:30,914
the Chambliss family?

00:16:30,914 --> 00:16:34,084
Calvin Chambliss and I
